    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Those look like fabulous ideas!</>I&#8217;m a big fan of soba noodles for long flights &#8212; I usually make up a batch of soba with a little fried tofu and some wasabe peas, and throw in lots of ginger and red pepper flakes;  after about four hours, it&#8217;s stimulating enough to make me feel better.  and the longer it sits, the more flavor the noodles soak up.</></>David Cheng&#8217;s recipe for < HREF="http://www.seriouseats.com/2007/02/noodling_around.html" REL="nofollow"> ginger scallion noodles<> is pretty fabulous.</p>
