      <p>Molly &#8211; love your blog! I am obsessed with frittatas, too. It is so easy, as you say. It&#8217;s now standard breakfast and dinner for hubby and me. I have an infrared broiler that the frittata adores &#8211; it puffs up and browns so nicely (2 min max). My standard ingredients are feta, **Mama Lil&#8217;s peppers**, onion, thinly slice Yukon Golds (if I have the time), and parm/romano on the top (just before broiler time). I haven&#8217;t felt need for non-stick. Maybe because I [heart] olive oil. Looking forward to the book!</p>
